    "collapsible_content_RfNcUx": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_row_VNGRLz": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What are electrolytes?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Electrolytes are charged minerals that conduct electricity to power your nervous system. The main electrolytes are sodium, chloride, potassium, magnesium, calcium, phosphorus and bicarbonate.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_NDJBRC": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Why do I need electrolytes?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Being low in electrolytes can lead to fatigue, cramps, headaches, and weakness. This is super common for keto and active folks, who lose more electrolytes through sweat and urine. Replacing electrolytes means better energy and less symptoms.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_QeBrRJ": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What are ketones?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Ketones are tiny molecules that fuel your body with alternate energy when carbs are scarce. There are three types of ketones: beta-hydroxybutyrate (BHB), acetoacetate, and acetone. BHB is your main energy ketone, and the active ingredient in Key Keto.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_CrHHwB": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What are exogenous ketones?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>Exogenous ketones are ketones that originate outside your body. They’re nearly identical to the ketones your body makes on a keto diet.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_dGxEcY": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Do I need to be on a low-carb diet to take Key Keto?",
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "row_content": "<p>No, exogenous ketones will elevate ketones even in the presence of carbs. Still, we recommend a keto diet for maximum synergy and benefits.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
